  "title": "Persistence Through Birth Compensation",
  "concept": "A population facing unavoidable harm can maintain size by increasing reproduction rates to match elevated mortality — the collective survives not by eliminating damage but by replacing losses faster.",
  "interactiveId": "0f8516f6-c081-4ae5-a693-88bdfa14b054",
  "sourcePieceId": "cee5e838-4718-4847-a229-b9271b6cb7ea",
  "publishedAt": 1777229645451,
  "voiceScore": 88,
  "qualityFlag": "low",
  "content": {
    "type": "html",
    "html": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\">\n<title>Persistence Through Birth Compensation</title>\n<style>\n:root {\n  --bg: #faf7f1;\n  --fg: #1a1a1a;\n  --muted: #6b6b6b;\n  --line: #e5e0d6;\n  --population: #1a6b62;\n  --mortality: #c94a4a;\n  --natality: #4a8ec9;\n}\n* { box-sizing: border-box; }\nbody {\n  font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, \"Segoe UI\", sans-serif;\n  margin: 0;\n  padding: 20px;\n  color: var(--fg);\n  background: var(--bg);\n  line-height: 1.5;\n}\nh2 {\n  font-size: 1.05rem;\n  font-weight: 600;\n  margin: 0 0 4px;\n}\np.subhead {\n  margin: 0 0 20px;\n  color: var(--muted);\n  font-size: 0.9rem;\n}\n.control {\n  display: flex;\n  align-items: center;\n  gap: 14px;\n  margin-bottom: 20px;\n}\n.control label {\n  font-weight: 500;\n  flex-shrink: 0;\n  min-width: 140px;\n}\n.control input[type=range] {\n  flex: 1;\n  accent-color: var(--mortality);\n  min-width: 120px;\n}\n.control output {\n  font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;\n  font-weight: 600;\n  min-width: 3ch;\n  text-align: right;\n}\n.dynamics {\n  margin: 24px 0;\n  background: #fff;\n  border: 1px solid var(--line);\n  border-radius: 6px;\n  padding: 20px;\n}\n.flow-diagram {\n  display: flex;\n  align-items: center;\n  justify-content: center;\n  gap: 24px;\n  margin: 20px 0;\n}\n.flow-box {\n  display: flex;\n  flex-direction: column;\n  align-items: center;\n  gap: 8px;\n}\n.flow-label {\n  font-size: 0.75rem;\n  text-transform: uppercase;\n  letter-spacing: 0.06em;\n  color: var(--muted);\n}\n.flow-value {\n  font-size: 1.5rem;\n  font-weight: 700;\n  font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;\n}\n.flow-box.births .flow-value { color: var(--natality); }\n.flow-box.deaths .flow-value { color: var(--mortality); }\n.flow-arrow {\n  font-size: 2rem;\n  color: var(--line);\n  line-height: 1;\n}\n.population-bar {\n  margin: 20px 0;\n  height: 60px;\n  background: var(--line);\n  border-radius: 4px;\n  overflow: hidden;\n  position: relative;\n}\n.population-fill {\n  height: 100%;\n  background: var(--population);\n  transition: width 200ms ease-out;\n  display: flex;\n  align-items: center;\n  justify-content: center;\n  color: #fff;\n  font-weight: 700;\n  font-size: 1.1rem;\n}\n.outcome {\n  margin-top: 16px;\n  padding: 14px;\n  background: #f9f9f9;\n  border-left: 3px solid var(--population);\n  border-radius: 3px;\n  text-align: center;\n}\n.outcome-label {\n  font-size: 0.85rem;\n  color: var(--muted);\n  margin-bottom: 4px;\n}\n.outcome-value {\n  font-size: 1.3rem;\n  font-weight: 700;\n  font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;\n}\n.outcome.growing { border-left-color: var(--natality); }\n.outcome.growing .outcome-value { color: var(--natality); }\n.outcome.stable { border-left-color: var(--population); }\n.outcome.stable .outcome-value { color: var(--population); }\n.outcome.declining { border-left-color: var(--mortality); }\n.outcome.declining .outcome-value { color: var(--mortality); }\np.caption {\n  margin: 16px 0 0;\n  color: var(--muted);\n  font-size: 0.875rem;\n  line-height: 1.6;\n}\n@media (max-width: 520px) {\n  .flow-diagram {\n    flex-direction: column;\n    gap: 12px;\n  }\n  .flow-arrow {\n    transform: rotate(90deg);\n  }\n  .control label {\n    min-width: 100px;\n    font-size: 0.9rem;\n  }\n}\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n<h2>Adjust mortality pressure</h2>\n<p class=\"subhead\">A constant-size population must balance births and deaths. Raise mortality; watch natality respond to preserve size.</p>\n\n<div class=\"control\">\n  <label for=\"mortality\">Mortality rate:</label>\n  <input id=\"mortality\" type=\"range\" min=\"5\" max=\"50\" value=\"15\" step=\"1\" aria-describedby=\"mortality-out\">\n  <output id=\"mortality-out\" for=\"mortality\">15</output>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"dynamics\">\n  <div class=\"flow-diagram\" aria-hidden=\"true\">\n    <div class=\"flow-box births\">\n      <span class=\"flow-label\">Births per 100</span>\n      <span class=\"flow-value\" id=\"births-value\">15</span>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"flow-arrow\">→</div>\n    <div class=\"flow-box\">\n      <span class=\"flow-label\">Population</span>\n      <span class=\"flow-value\" style=\"color: var(--population);\" id=\"pop-value\">100</span>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"flow-arrow\">→</div>\n    <div class=\"flow-box deaths\">\n      <span class=\"flow-label\">Deaths per 100</span>\n      <span class=\"flow-value\" id=\"deaths-value\">15</span>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"population-bar\" aria-hidden=\"true\">\n    <div class=\"population-fill\" id=\"pop-fill\">100</div>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"outcome\" id=\"outcome\">\n    <div class=\"outcome-label\">Net change per cycle</div>\n    <div class=\"outcome-value\" id=\"net-change\">0</div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"caption\" id=\"caption\">Low mortality. Births match deaths at a modest rate. Population holds steady with minimal churn.</p>\n\n<script>\n(function () {\n  var slider = document.getElementById('mortality');\n  var mortalityOut = document.getElementById('mortality-out');\n  var birthsValue = document.getElementById('births-value');\n  var deathsValue = document.getElementById('deaths-value');\n  var popValue = document.getElementById('pop-value');\n  var popFill = document.getElementById('pop-fill');\n  var netChange = document.getElementById('net-change');\n  var caption = document.getElementById('caption');\n  var outcome = document.getElementById('outcome');\n\n  var basePopulation = 100;\n\n  function clamp(val, min, max) {\n    return Math.max(min, Math.min(max, val));\n  }\n\n  function update() {\n    var mortality = +slider.value;\n    mortalityOut.textContent = mortality;\n\n    var natality = mortality + Math.floor((mortality - 15) * 0.08);\n    natality = clamp(natality, 5, 55);\n\n    var deaths = mortality;\n    var births = natality;\n    var net = births - deaths;\n    var population = basePopulation + net * 2;\n    population = clamp(population, 50, 150);\n\n    birthsValue.textContent = births;\n    deathsValue.textContent = deaths;\n    popValue.textContent = population;\n    popFill.textContent = population;\n    popFill.style.width = population + '%';\n\n    var netSign = net >= 0 ? '+' : '';\n    netChange.textContent = netSign + net;\n\n    if (net > 2) {\n      outcome.className = 'outcome growing';\n    } else if (net >= -2) {\n      outcome.className = 'outcome stable';\n    } else {\n      outcome.className = 'outcome declining';\n    }\n\n    if (mortality < 15) {\n      caption.textContent = 'Low mortality. Births match deaths at a modest rate. Population holds steady with minimal churn.';\n    } else if (mortality < 25) {\n      caption.textContent = 'Moderate mortality. Death rate rises; birth rate climbs to compensate. Population stays stable through higher replacement.';\n    } else if (mortality < 35) {\n      caption.textContent = 'High mortality. Many members lost each cycle. Birth rate elevated to fill the gap. Size holds only because arrivals offset exits.';\n    } else if (mortality < 45) {\n      caption.textContent = 'Severe mortality. Losses accumulate fast. Natality near maximum to keep population from collapsing. Stability depends entirely on rapid replacement.';\n    } else {\n      caption.textContent = 'Extreme mortality. Birth rate at ceiling, cannot rise further. Losses exceed replacements. Population begins terminal decline.';\n    }\n  }\n\n  slider.addEventListener('input', update);\n  update();\n})();\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>"
  }
}
